The paper discusses the application of conversation analysis principles to the design of technologies that enhance human conversation. This suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the design of an electronic guidebook, which could fall under the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE) or human-centered computing (cs.HC). The discussion of social, mobile audio spaces suggests a focus on social and information retrieval (cs.SD) or cybernetics (cs.CY).
